{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":760,"text":"This is what my last week looked like."},{"time":4680,"text":"What I did,"},{"time":6400,"text":"who I was with,"},{"time":8240,"text":"the main sensations I had\nfor every waking hour ..."},{"time":12080,"text":"If the feeling came as I thought of my dad"},{"time":14600,"text":"who recently passed away,"},{"time":16400,"text":"or if I could have just definitely\navoided the worries and anxieties."},{"time":20480,"text":"And if you think I'm a little obsessive,"},{"time":22440,"text":"you're probably right."},{"time":24320,"text":"But clearly, from this visualization,"},{"time":26600,"text":"you can learn much more about me\nthan from this other one,"},{"time":29920,"text":"which are images you're\nprobably more familiar with"},{"time":32920,"text":"and which you possibly even have\non your phone right now."},{"time":35760,"text":"Bar charts for the steps you walked,"},{"time":38000,"text":"pie charts for the quality\nof your sleep --"},{"time":40400,"text":"the path of your morning runs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":43280,"text":"In my day job, I work with data."},{"time":45600,"text":"I run a data visualization design company,"},{"time":48120,"text":"and we design and develop ways\nto make information accessible"},{"time":51480,"text":"through visual representations."},{"time":53600,"text":"What my job has taught me over the years"},{"time":56640,"text":"is that to really understand data\nand their true potential,"},{"time":60880,"text":"sometimes we actually\nhave to forget about them"},{"time":64000,"text":"and see through them instead."},{"time":66440,"text":"Because data are always\njust a tool we use to represent reality."},{"time":70040,"text":"They're always used\nas a placeholder for something else,"},{"time":72920,"text":"but they are never the real thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":75120,"text":"But let me step back for a moment"},{"time":77080,"text":"to when I first understood\nthis personally."},{"time":80280,"text":"In 1994, I was 13 years old."},{"time":83640,"text":"I was a teenager in Italy."},{"time":85600,"text":"I was too young\nto be interested in politics,"},{"time":88240,"text":"but I knew that a businessman,\nSilvio Berlusconi,"},{"time":90760,"text":"was running for president\nfor the moderate right."},{"time":94120,"text":"We lived in a very liberal town,"},{"time":96160,"text":"and my father was a politician\nfor the Democratic Party."},{"time":99480,"text":"And I remember that no one thought\nthat Berlusconi could get elected --"},{"time":103840,"text":"that was totally not an option."},{"time":106560,"text":"But it happened."},{"time":107800,"text":"And I remember the feeling very vividly."},{"time":110360,"text":"It was a complete surprise,"},{"time":112240,"text":"as my dad promised that in my town\nhe knew nobody who voted for him."}]},{"cues":[{"time":118720,"text":"This was the first time"},{"time":120240,"text":"when the data I had gave me\na completely distorted image of reality."},{"time":125280,"text":"My data sample was actually\npretty limited and skewed,"},{"time":128600,"text":"so probably it was because of that,\nI thought, I lived in a bubble,"},{"time":132360,"text":"and I didn't have enough chances\nto see outside of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":136080,"text":"Now, fast-forward to November 8, 2016"},{"time":139880,"text":"in the United States."},{"time":141960,"text":"The internet polls,"},{"time":143280,"text":"statistical models,"},{"time":144680,"text":"all the pundits agreeing on a possible\noutcome for the presidential election."},{"time":149520,"text":"It looked like we had\nenough information this time,"},{"time":152160,"text":"and many more chances to see outside\nthe closed circle we lived in --"},{"time":156280,"text":"but we clearly didn't."},{"time":158040,"text":"The feeling felt very familiar."},{"time":160160,"text":"I had been there before."},{"time":162360,"text":"I think it's fair to say\nthe data failed us this time --"},{"time":165240,"text":"and pretty spectacularly."},{"time":167120,"text":"We believed in data,"},{"time":168840,"text":"but what happened,"},{"time":170280,"text":"even with the most respected newspaper,"},{"time":173000,"text":"is that the obsession to reduce everything\nto two simple percentage numbers"},{"time":177720,"text":"to make a powerful headline"},{"time":179720,"text":"made us focus on these two digits"},{"time":181800,"text":"and them alone."},{"time":183560,"text":"In an effort to simplify the message"},{"time":185640,"text":"and draw a beautiful,\ninevitable red and blue map,"},{"time":189080,"text":"we lost the point completely."},{"time":191440,"text":"We somehow forgot\nthat there were stories --"},{"time":193600,"text":"stories of human beings\nbehind these numbers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":197240,"text":"In a different context,"},{"time":198840,"text":"but to a very similar point,"},{"time":200520,"text":"a peculiar challenge was presented\nto my team by this woman."},{"time":204440,"text":"She came to us with a lot of data,"},{"time":206840,"text":"but ultimately she wanted to tell\none of the most humane stories possible."},{"time":211280,"text":"She's Samantha Cristoforetti."},{"time":213000,"text":"She has been the first\nItalian woman astronaut,"},{"time":215600,"text":"and she contacted us before being launched"},{"time":218120,"text":"on a six-month-long expedition\nto the International Space Station."},{"time":222040,"text":"She told us, \"I'm going to space,"},{"time":224280,"text":"and I want to do something meaningful\nwith the data of my mission"},{"time":227400,"text":"to reach out to people.\""},{"time":229600,"text":"A mission to the\nInternational Space Station"},{"time":232160,"text":"comes with terabytes of data"},{"time":234280,"text":"about anything you can possibly imagine --"},{"time":236680,"text":"the orbits around Earth,"},{"time":238200,"text":"the speed and position of the ISS"},{"time":240320,"text":"and all of the other thousands\nof live streams from its sensors."},{"time":244840,"text":"We had all of the hard data\nwe could think of --"},{"time":247760,"text":"just like the pundits\nbefore the election --"},{"time":250200,"text":"but what is the point\nof all these numbers?"},{"time":253200,"text":"People are not interested\nin data for the sake of it,"},{"time":255960,"text":"because numbers are never the point."},{"time":257839,"text":"They're always the means to an end."},{"time":260839,"text":"The story we needed to tell"},{"time":262640,"text":"is that there is a human being\nin a teeny box"},{"time":265160,"text":"flying in space above your head,"},{"time":267440,"text":"and that you can actually see her\nwith your naked eye on a clear night."},{"time":271560,"text":"So we decided to use data\nto create a connection"},{"time":274680,"text":"between Samantha and all of the people\nlooking at her from below."},{"time":278760,"text":"We designed and developed\nwhat we called \"Friends in Space,\""},{"time":281960,"text":"a web application that simply\nlets you say \"hello\" to Samantha"},{"time":286640,"text":"from where you are,"},{"time":287920,"text":"and \"hello\" to all the people\nwho are online at the same time"},{"time":291480,"text":"from all over the world."},{"time":293640,"text":"And all of these \"hellos\"\nleft visible marks on the map"},{"time":297120,"text":"as Samantha was flying by"},{"time":299160,"text":"and as she was actually\nwaving back every day at us"},{"time":302560,"text":"using Twitter from the ISS."}]},{"cues":[{"time":304880,"text":"This made people see the mission's data\nfrom a very different perspective."},{"time":309880,"text":"It all suddenly became much more\nabout our human nature and our curiosity,"},{"time":314600,"text":"rather than technology."},{"time":316280,"text":"So data powered the experience,"},{"time":318640,"text":"but stories of human beings\nwere the drive."},{"time":322840,"text":"The very positive response\nof its thousands of users"},{"time":326200,"text":"taught me a very important lesson --"},{"time":328160,"text":"that working with data\nmeans designing ways"},{"time":331040,"text":"to transform the abstract\nand the uncountable"},{"time":333800,"text":"into something that can be seen,\nfelt and directly reconnected"},{"time":337840,"text":"to our lives and to our behaviors,"},{"time":340160,"text":"something that is hard to achieve"},{"time":342040,"text":"if we let the obsession for the numbers\nand the technology around them"},{"time":345960,"text":"lead us in the process."},{"time":348600,"text":"But we can do even more to connect data\nto the stories they represent."},{"time":353520,"text":"We can remove technology completely."}]},{"cues":[{"time":356200,"text":"A few years ago, I met this other woman,"},{"time":358480,"text":"Stefanie Posavec --"},{"time":359880,"text":"a London-based designer who shares with me\nthe passion and obsession about data."},{"time":365720,"text":"We didn't know each other,"},{"time":367080,"text":"but we decided to run\na very radical experiment,"},{"time":370360,"text":"starting a communication using only data,"},{"time":372920,"text":"no other language,"},{"time":374280,"text":"and we opted for using no technology\nwhatsoever to share our data."},{"time":378920,"text":"In fact, our only means of communication"},{"time":381840,"text":"would be through\nthe old-fashioned post office."},{"time":384720,"text":"For \"Dear Data,\" every week for one year,"},{"time":387200,"text":"we used our personal data\nto get to know each other --"},{"time":390680,"text":"personal data around weekly\nshared mundane topics,"},{"time":394360,"text":"from our feelings"},{"time":395600,"text":"to the interactions with our partners,"},{"time":397480,"text":"from the compliments we received\nto the sounds of our surroundings."},{"time":401480,"text":"Personal information\nthat we would then manually hand draw"},{"time":405040,"text":"on a postcard-size sheet of paper"},{"time":407560,"text":"that we would every week\nsend from London to New York,"},{"time":410520,"text":"where I live,"},{"time":411800,"text":"and from New York to London,\nwhere she lives."},{"time":414480,"text":"The front of the postcard\nis the data drawing,"},{"time":418200,"text":"and the back of the card"},{"time":419520,"text":"contains the address\nof the other person, of course,"},{"time":421973,"text":"and the legend for how\nto interpret our drawing."},{"time":425640,"text":"The very first week into the project,"},{"time":427680,"text":"we actually chose\na pretty cold and impersonal topic."},{"time":430760,"text":"How many times do we\ncheck the time in a week?"},{"time":434720,"text":"So here is the front of my card,"},{"time":436680,"text":"and you can see that every little symbol"},{"time":438680,"text":"represents all of the times\nthat I checked the time,"},{"time":442120,"text":"positioned for days\nand different hours chronologically --"},{"time":445520,"text":"nothing really complicated here."},{"time":448200,"text":"But then you see in the legend"},{"time":449800,"text":"how I added anecdotal details\nabout these moments."},{"time":453280,"text":"In fact, the different types of symbols\nindicate why I was checking the time --"},{"time":457880,"text":"what was I doing?"},{"time":459120,"text":"Was I bored? Was I hungry?"},{"time":460840,"text":"Was I late?"},{"time":462080,"text":"Did I check it on purpose\nor just casually glance at the clock?"},{"time":465320,"text":"And this is the key part --"},{"time":467600,"text":"representing the details\nof my days and my personality"},{"time":471320,"text":"through my data collection."},{"time":473280,"text":"Using data as a lens or a filter\nto discover and reveal, for example,"},{"time":478000,"text":"my never-ending anxiety for being late,"},{"time":480200,"text":"even though I'm absolutely always on time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":484200,"text":"Stefanie and I spent one year\ncollecting our data manually"},{"time":488320,"text":"to force us to focus on the nuances\nthat computers cannot gather --"},{"time":492840,"text":"or at least not yet --"},{"time":494400,"text":"using data also to explore our minds\nand the words we use,"},{"time":497920,"text":"and not only our activities."},{"time":499880,"text":"Like at week number three,"},{"time":501320,"text":"where we tracked the \"thank yous\"\nwe said and were received,"},{"time":505160,"text":"and when I realized that I thank\nmostly people that I don't know."},{"time":509840,"text":"Apparently I'm a compulsive thanker\nto waitresses and waiters,"},{"time":514200,"text":"but I definitely don't thank enough\nthe people who are close to me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":519000,"text":"Over one year,"},{"time":520280,"text":"the process of actively noticing\nand counting these types of actions"},{"time":524800,"text":"became a ritual."},{"time":526120,"text":"It actually changed ourselves."},{"time":528200,"text":"We became much more\nin tune with ourselves,"},{"time":530920,"text":"much more aware of our behaviors\nand our surroundings."},{"time":534680,"text":"Over one year, Stefanie and I\nconnected at a very deep level"},{"time":537680,"text":"through our shared data diary,"},{"time":539720,"text":"but we could do this only because\nwe put ourselves in these numbers,"},{"time":544040,"text":"adding the contexts\nof our very personal stories to them."},{"time":548040,"text":"It was the only way\nto make them truly meaningful"},{"time":550520,"text":"and representative of ourselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":554480,"text":"I am not asking you\nto start drawing your personal data,"},{"time":557600,"text":"or to find a pen pal across the ocean."},{"time":560480,"text":"But I'm asking you to consider data --"},{"time":563080,"text":"all kind of data --"},{"time":564560,"text":"as the beginning of the conversation"},{"time":566360,"text":"and not the end."},{"time":568080,"text":"Because data alone\nwill never give us a solution."},{"time":571280,"text":"And this is why data failed us so badly --"},{"time":574000,"text":"because we failed to include\nthe right amount of context"},{"time":577400,"text":"to represent reality --"},{"time":578880,"text":"a nuanced, complicated\nand intricate reality."},{"time":582960,"text":"We kept looking at these two numbers,"},{"time":585440,"text":"obsessing with them"},{"time":586960,"text":"and pretending that our world\ncould be reduced"},{"time":589480,"text":"to a couple digits and a horse race,"},{"time":591840,"text":"while the real stories,"},{"time":593120,"text":"the ones that really mattered,"},{"time":594600,"text":"were somewhere else."}]},{"cues":[{"time":596040,"text":"What we missed looking at these stories\nonly through models and algorithms"},{"time":600480,"text":"is what I call \"data humanism.\""},{"time":603560,"text":"In the Renaissance humanism,"},{"time":605600,"text":"European intellectuals"},{"time":607240,"text":"placed the human nature instead of God\nat the center of their view of the world."},{"time":612800,"text":"I believe something similar\nneeds to happen"},{"time":615040,"text":"with the universe of data."},{"time":616840,"text":"Now data are apparently\ntreated like a God --"},{"time":619840,"text":"keeper of infallible truth\nfor our present and our future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":623840,"text":"The experiences\nthat I shared with you today"},{"time":626760,"text":"taught me that to make data faithfully\nrepresentative of our human nature"},{"time":631800,"text":"and to make sure they will not\nmislead us anymore,"},{"time":635240,"text":"we need to start designing ways\nto include empathy, imperfection"},{"time":638960,"text":"and human qualities"},{"time":640560,"text":"in how we collect, process,\nanalyze and display them."},{"time":645280,"text":"I do see a place where, ultimately,"},{"time":648280,"text":"instead of using data\nonly to become more efficient,"},{"time":651640,"text":"we will all use data\nto become more humane."}]},{"cues":[{"time":654880,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":656120,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}